01:13:04.778 --> 01:13:08.082
They have to listen to us now.

01:13:25.698 --> 01:13:27.598
Dr. Maroon.

01:13:27.600 --> 01:13:29.968
- Would you like a drink?
- I said five minutes.

01:13:29.970 --> 01:13:32.137
He doesn't want a drink.

01:13:32.139 --> 01:13:35.706
Your conclusions totally
misrepresent the facts.

01:13:35.708 --> 01:13:39.076
To say that Webster and Long and
Waters were killed by football is...

01:13:39.078 --> 01:13:41.979
Is fallacious reasoning.

01:13:41.981 --> 01:13:45.083
Yes, I know.

01:13:45.085 --> 01:13:47.552
Where's he going with this?

01:13:47.554 --> 01:13:50.155
Just hear him out.

01:13:50.157 --> 01:13:53.924
I would like to propose
a formal, controlled study

01:13:53.926 --> 01:13:57.795
of former and current NFL football players.

01:13:57.797 --> 01:14:00.531
We will bring together the greatest minds

01:14:00.533 --> 01:14:02.701
in America to solve the problem.

01:14:02.703 --> 01:14:04.505
We should be working together.

01:14:06.273 --> 01:14:09.907
Who do you think you're talking to?

01:14:09.909 --> 01:14:11.210
Excuse me?

01:14:11.212 --> 01:14:15.112
I was the President of the
Congress of Neurological Surgeons.

01:14:15.114 --> 01:14:18.250
And I was the man who
performed the autopsies

01:14:18.252 --> 01:14:21.852
on Mike Webster, Terry Long.

01:14:21.854 --> 01:14:24.522
Your men.

01:14:24.524 --> 01:14:26.727
Men under your care.

01:14:29.095 --> 01:14:31.929
Do you know what Mike Webster's wife said?

01:14:31.931 --> 01:14:36.736
She said that if she had
known that Mike was sick,

01:14:38.305 --> 01:14:41.275
she would have done more for him.

01:14:43.243 --> 01:14:48.045
But he died in disgrace.

01:14:48.047 --> 01:14:49.616
Your man.

01:14:51.083 --> 01:14:53.151
Your man.

01:14:53.153 --> 01:14:55.954
You took an oath.

01:14:55.956 --> 01:14:57.888
- Tell the truth.
- The truth?

01:14:57.890 --> 01:15:00.959
- Tell the truth!
- The truth is

01:15:00.961 --> 01:15:05.465
that the NFL is a blessing
and a salvation, my friend.

01:15:06.966 --> 01:15:10.000
We employ hundreds of thousands of people.

01:15:10.002 --> 01:15:14.071
We send thousands and thousands
of poor kids to school.

01:15:14.073 --> 01:15:16.775
The ownership of this football club

01:15:16.777 --> 01:15:20.611
has donated millions of
dollars to countless charities.

01:15:20.613 --> 01:15:22.046
Do you want me to go on?

01:15:22.048 --> 01:15:23.581
That won't be necessary.

01:15:23.583 --> 01:15:25.916
Oh, it is necessary.

01:15:25.918 --> 01:15:30.254
Football is the most
popular sport in America

01:15:30.256 --> 01:15:33.325
because it is so goddamn fantastic!

01:15:36.796 --> 01:15:39.365
And that, right there?

01:15:40.634 --> 01:15:44.835
That is the beating heart of this city.

01:15:44.837 --> 01:15:47.071
And you want to, what, end it?

01:15:47.073 --> 01:15:51.343
You want to fold up the
National Football League?

01:15:51.345 --> 01:15:53.644
I want to solve the problem.

01:15:53.646 --> 01:15:55.679
Who are you?

01:15:55.681 --> 01:15:56.947
What are you asking?

01:15:56.949 --> 01:15:58.817
You're a pathologist.

01:15:58.819 --> 01:16:00.718
You perform autopsies.

01:16:00.720 --> 01:16:02.219
Yes, I am a mere pathologist.

01:16:02.221 --> 01:16:04.690
That's it. That's all I am.

01:16:09.630 --> 01:16:12.363
Wow.

01:16:12.365 --> 01:16:15.700
Do you have any idea of the
impact of what you're doing?

01:16:15.702 --> 01:16:16.901
Yes, I do.

01:16:16.903 --> 01:16:18.335
Do you understand the impact

01:16:18.337 --> 01:16:20.371
of what you are doing?

01:16:20.373 --> 01:16:24.174
If just 10% of the mothers in America

01:16:24.176 --> 01:16:26.977
decide that football is too
dangerous for their sons to play,

01:16:26.979 --> 01:16:30.815
that is it. It is the end of football.

01:16:30.817 --> 01:16:33.418
Kids, colleges, and eventually, it's just

01:16:33.420 --> 01:16:36.254
a matter of time, the professional game.

01:16:36.256 --> 01:16:39.758
Joe, he does autopsies. He's
not in the outcome business.

01:16:39.760 --> 01:16:41.992
He has no business.

01:16:41.994 --> 01:16:45.863
Do you know what history does to people,

01:16:45.865 --> 01:16:48.133
trained physicians,

01:16:48.135 --> 01:16:50.268
- who ignore science?
- Oh, wow.

01:16:50.270 --> 01:16:52.370
Sir, I am not done!

01:16:52.372 --> 01:16:54.574
History laughs.

01:16:55.908 --> 01:16:58.942
If you continue to deny my work,

01:16:58.944 --> 01:17:01.614
the world will deny my work.

01:17:03.050 --> 01:17:06.920
But men, your men,

01:17:08.087 --> 01:17:12.459
continue to die, their
families left in ruins.

01:17:15.729 --> 01:17:17.730
Tell the truth.

01:17:19.298 --> 01:17:21.468
Tell the truth.

01:17:32.345 --> 01:17:36.281
You sure... You sure you want to do this?

01:17:36.283 --> 01:17:39.820
I would ask you that
same question, Dr. Maroon.

01:17:43.957 --> 01:17:47.494
Oh, your study, I'll get back to you.

01:17:59.939 --> 01:18:02.408
Well, that went well.

01:18:42.282 --> 01:18:46.553
When I was a boy growing up in Nigeria,

01:18:49.855 --> 01:18:55.995
heaven was here and America was here.

01:18:58.864 --> 01:19:03.469
To me, it was the place where God
sent all of His favorite people.

01:19:05.372 --> 01:19:08.708
You could be anything,
you could do anything.

01:19:10.277 --> 01:19:12.977
Americans were the manifestation

01:19:12.979 --> 01:19:15.515
of what God wanted us all to be.

01:19:20.020 --> 01:19:24.421
I have never wanted anything

01:19:24.423 --> 01:19:27.993
as much as I wanted to be
accepted as an American.

01:19:34.033 --> 01:19:39.038
But Mike Webster goes
mad and nobody asks why.

01:19:41.106 --> 01:19:43.340
They make fun of him.

01:19:43.342 --> 01:19:45.943
They insult him on TV.

01:19:45.945 --> 01:19:48.612
And now they want to pretend
that his disease does not exist.

01:19:48.614 --> 01:19:51.617
And they want to bury me.

01:19:54.554 --> 01:19:56.756
It's offensive.

01:19:58.324 --> 01:20:00.893
I am offended.

01:20:06.198 --> 01:20:10.535
I am the wrong person
to have discovered this.

01:20:14.039 --> 01:20:17.743
There is no coincidence in this world.

01:20:19.645 --> 01:20:22.347
Tell me,

01:20:22.349 --> 01:20:28.085
what is the statistical probability
that you, not just a doctor,

01:20:28.087 --> 01:20:33.156
but Bennet Omalu, came to America,

01:20:33.158 --> 01:20:36.361
ended up here in this rusty place

01:20:36.363 --> 01:20:40.600
for you alone to be the one to see this?

01:20:47.506 --> 01:20:50.142
When I arrived in New York,

01:20:51.511 --> 01:20:53.644
I was attacked.

01:20:53.646 --> 01:20:55.345
What happened?

01:20:55.347 --> 01:20:58.585
Something that is better left unsaid.

01:21:00.052 --> 01:21:03.989
But that man almost broke me.

01:21:05.926 --> 01:21:09.829
I wanted to give up and go back.

01:21:13.265 --> 01:21:15.768
But I knew God.

01:21:17.136 --> 01:21:22.741
I decided to trust His wisdom and I stayed.

01:21:25.110 --> 01:21:29.647
And now I am looking at this man,

01:21:29.649 --> 01:21:33.116
an Omalu Onyemalukwube.

01:21:33.118 --> 01:21:38.089
Your name, it means, "If you know,

01:21:38.091 --> 01:21:40.794
"you must come forth and speak."

01:21:42.561 --> 01:21:44.528
How did you know that?

01:21:44.530 --> 01:21:46.363
I called your father.

01:21:46.365 --> 01:21:48.098
He was pleased to hear from me.

01:21:48.100 --> 01:21:51.302
Yes, I am sure he was.

01:21:51.304 --> 01:21:54.908
If you don't speak for the dead, who will?

01:21:56.676 --> 01:21:59.643
You are of the Igbo tribe, Bennet.

01:21:59.645 --> 01:22:02.179
When you have truth,

01:22:02.181 --> 01:22:03.447
the thing you are told you cannot do

01:22:03.449 --> 01:22:05.983
is the thing you must do.

01:22:05.985 --> 01:22:08.318
Embrace that

01:22:08.320 --> 01:22:12.625
and nothing created by
man can bring you down.

01:22:19.064 --> 01:22:22.733
Omalu's gone to the
press now. Listen to this.

01:22:22.735 --> 01:22:25.068
"After examining the remains

01:22:25.070 --> 01:22:27.772
"of former National Football
League player Andre Waters,

01:22:27.774 --> 01:22:32.175
"a neuropathologist in Pittsburgh,
Dr. Bennet Omalu, is claiming

01:22:32.177 --> 01:22:34.245
"that Mr. Waters had sustained brain damage

01:22:34.247 --> 01:22:36.546
"from playing football, and he says

01:22:36.548 --> 01:22:41.085
"that led to his depression
and ultimate death."

01:22:41.087 --> 01:22:43.687
It gets worse.

01:22:43.689 --> 01:22:45.690
"Dr. Julian Bailes, medical director

01:22:45.692 --> 01:22:48.092
"for the Center for the
Study of Retired Athletes

01:22:48.094 --> 01:22:49.360
"and the chairman of the Department of

01:22:49.362 --> 01:22:52.095
"Neurosurgery of West Virginia University,

01:22:52.097 --> 01:22:55.366
"said, 'Unfortunately, I'm not shocked.'"

01:22:55.368 --> 01:22:58.135
There's more Omalu and more Bailes.

01:22:58.137 --> 01:23:00.772
Bailes. Why do I know that name?

01:23:00.774 --> 01:23:04.541
Steelers team doctor. Neurologist
for the Players Association.

01:23:07.212 --> 01:23:09.513
- Wow.
- Yeah, wow.

01:23:09.515 --> 01:23:12.583
The <i>Times</i> is calling
it a potential epidemic.

01:23:12.585 --> 01:23:14.220
Paul.

01:23:15.488 --> 01:23:19.156
It's not the Sports section, not Science.

01:23:19.158 --> 01:23:23.896
It's A-1, front page
<i>New York Times.</i>

01:23:27.466 --> 01:23:29.134
<i>Apparently, the Commissioner</i>

01:23:29.136 --> 01:23:32.335
<i>has been yearning for years to
go back to his litigator roots.</i>

01:23:32.337 --> 01:23:35.705
<i>Paul Tagliabue announced
that he would retire in July</i>

01:23:35.707 --> 01:23:38.342
<i>after nearly 17 years.</i>

01:23:38.344 --> 01:23:40.544
<i>...comprised the most lucrative</i>

01:23:40.546 --> 01:23:43.680
<i>and stabilizing reign
perhaps in the history.</i>

01:23:43.682 --> 01:23:46.384
<i>At the NFL owners meeting in
Illinois, Roger Goodell...</i>

01:23:46.386 --> 01:23:49.553
<i>There's a new sheriff in town.
His name is Roger Goodell.</i>

01:23:49.555 --> 01:23:51.822
<i>Each day seems to bring a
fresh round of tributes.</i>

01:23:51.824 --> 01:23:54.558
<i>What I'm here to do now
is protect the shield.</i>

01:23:54.560 --> 01:23:58.295
<i>The NFL isn't just a sports league.</i>

01:23:58.297 --> 01:23:59.830
<i>It's an entertainment product.</i>

01:23:59.832 --> 01:24:02.299
<i>America's game.</i>

01:24:02.301 --> 01:24:04.335
<i>I want us to go on
enjoying our great game...</i>

01:24:04.337 --> 01:24:05.803
Allegheny County Coroner.

01:24:05.805 --> 01:24:08.873
Sure, one second.

01:24:08.875 --> 01:24:11.209
- It's Dr. Julian Bailes.
- Yes, yeah.

01:24:11.211 --> 01:24:13.844
Here he is.

01:24:13.846 --> 01:24:15.178
Julian.

01:24:15.180 --> 01:24:16.580
<i>Hey, turn on the TV.</i>

01:24:16.582 --> 01:24:18.250
Yes, I'm watching.

01:24:18.252 --> 01:24:22.452
<i>You asked for a face-to-face with
the Commissioner? Man to man?</i>

01:24:22.454 --> 01:24:26.590
<i>Goodell and the NFL are asking
for a concussion summit.</i>

01:24:26.592 --> 01:24:30.894
<i>A full presentation
in Chicago next week.</i>

01:24:30.896 --> 01:24:33.330
<i>They heard you.</i>

01:24:33.332 --> 01:24:35.234
<i>You have your shot.</i>

01:24:36.469 --> 01:24:38.138
Julian.

01:24:52.351 --> 01:24:54.652
Why don't you throw in some football stuff?

01:24:54.654 --> 01:24:56.786
Some non-medical terms?

01:24:56.788 --> 01:24:59.357
Things we'd say.

01:24:59.359 --> 01:25:02.162
Why do I need to say things they'd say?

01:25:03.262 --> 01:25:05.530
I thought I was here for the other reason.

01:25:05.532 --> 01:25:06.930
No.

01:25:06.932 --> 01:25:09.333
You have what, seven, eight degrees?

01:25:09.335 --> 01:25:10.601
You're one of the smartest people

01:25:10.603 --> 01:25:14.504
they'll ever meet. You... Well...

01:25:14.506 --> 01:25:16.507
You know what?

01:25:16.509 --> 01:25:18.845
You're gonna be fine.

01:25:27.686 --> 01:25:29.922
How about you?

01:25:31.224 --> 01:25:33.193
How will you be?

01:25:37.630 --> 01:25:44.201
You know, it is a mindless, violent
game and then it's Shakespeare.

01:25:44.203 --> 01:25:46.236
<i>I mean, to me it's
like life that way.</i>

01:25:46.238 --> 01:25:49.906
<i>And I know you can't
see how exciting</i>

01:25:49.908 --> 01:25:53.979
and beautiful all that
is, and I don't blame you.

01:25:55.247 --> 01:26:00.419
But what I'm trying to tell
you is this is not fun for me.

01:26:01.954 --> 01:26:03.653
All of the people we're going to

01:26:03.655 --> 01:26:05.289
see tomorrow, I know them personally.

01:26:05.291 --> 01:26:06.924
And that feeling you have

01:26:06.926 --> 01:26:11.998
when someone you love and
admire screws you over?

01:26:14.667 --> 01:26:17.403
They're going to have that feeling.

01:26:19.271 --> 01:26:21.273
Because of me.

01:26:22.507 --> 01:26:25.377
And there is not a damn
thing I can do about it.

01:26:45.597 --> 01:26:46.731
Hey.

01:26:46.733 --> 01:26:48.398
We have to talk.

01:26:48.400 --> 01:26:50.236
What's wrong?

01:26:52.805 --> 01:26:56.339
There's no easy way to say this,
so I'm just going to say it.

01:26:56.341 --> 01:26:58.310
They're not gonna let you speak.

01:26:59.578 --> 01:27:01.611
What?

01:27:01.613 --> 01:27:04.182
They don't even want you in the room.

01:27:06.351 --> 01:27:08.187
They want me to do it.

01:27:10.590 --> 01:27:12.757
- One of their own.
- One of their own.

01:27:12.759 --> 01:27:13.657
So, they want to pretend...

01:27:13.659 --> 01:27:15.826
That you don't even exist, that's right.

01:27:15.828 --> 01:27:17.727
Okay. Yeah.

01:27:17.729 --> 01:27:20.330
- They still have to sit and listen.
- To you.

01:27:20.332 --> 01:27:22.666
Yes. You blew up their whole world.

01:27:22.668 --> 01:27:24.035
And yours, Julian.

01:27:24.037 --> 01:27:26.736
Yes. Mine.

01:27:26.738 --> 01:27:32.876
Because how can it be possible
that some African voodoo doctor

01:27:32.878 --> 01:27:36.513
could understand this
subject better than them?

01:27:36.515 --> 01:27:39.817
Or even better than you?

01:27:39.819 --> 01:27:42.952
Wait a second. You think
this is about Bennet Omalu?

01:27:42.954 --> 01:27:45.955
I'm not here because of you. I'm
here because people are dying.

01:27:45.957 --> 01:27:47.924
You are here for redemption.

01:27:47.926 --> 01:27:51.363
You are here to use me
to cleanse your sins.

01:27:52.965 --> 01:27:56.400
You self-righteous bastard.

01:27:56.402 --> 01:28:00.403
Do you have any idea what I
could have, how much I could have

01:28:00.405 --> 01:28:05.111
if I went back to my side of the
ball and just kept my mouth shut?

01:28:06.612 --> 01:28:08.379
Everything in my world is telling me

01:28:08.381 --> 01:28:11.014
not to agree with you, except one.

01:28:11.016 --> 01:28:13.351
Science.

01:28:13.353 --> 01:28:16.053
So, here I am.

01:28:16.055 --> 01:28:20.560
Up here, beside you. Not down
there in that audience with them.

01:28:22.395 --> 01:28:26.032
What more can I do to prove myself to you?

01:28:54.694 --> 01:28:56.562
I am sorry.

01:28:58.497 --> 01:29:01.066
Convince them, Julian.

01:29:17.649 --> 01:29:20.017
You know, my father can't
remember a goddamn thing.

01:29:20.019 --> 01:29:22.152
He never played a day of football.

01:29:22.154 --> 01:29:25.156
He was too busy working
in a factory, you quack!

01:29:25.158 --> 01:29:27.057
I beg your pardon?

01:29:27.059 --> 01:29:29.960
You take your bullshit
science, go back to Africa.

01:29:29.962 --> 01:29:31.597
And get away from our game!

01:29:34.934 --> 01:29:36.767
What happened?

01:29:36.769 --> 01:29:38.936
Roger Goodell just said that

01:29:38.938 --> 01:29:42.906
Justin Strzelczyk may have
gotten his concussion swimming.

01:29:42.908 --> 01:29:44.174
In a swimming pool.

01:29:44.176 --> 01:29:45.776
That's insanity.

01:29:45.778 --> 01:29:48.111
This whole thing was staged.

01:29:48.113 --> 01:29:50.848
They needed to say that they heard
us so they could goddamn bury us.

01:29:50.850 --> 01:29:53.550
The science means nothing to them.

01:29:53.552 --> 01:29:54.919
<i>This is an important day</i>

01:29:54.921 --> 01:29:56.786
<i>in the National Football League.</i>

01:29:56.788 --> 01:29:59.156
<i>We've had some very good dialogue</i>

01:29:59.158 --> 01:30:03.227
<i>which will help us improve
the care for our players.</i>

01:30:03.229 --> 01:30:05.196
<i>What do you think
when you hear about</i>

01:30:05.198 --> 01:30:08.098
<i>former NFL players
suffering from symptoms</i>

01:30:08.100 --> 01:30:09.700
<i>that has only been seen in boxers</i>

01:30:09.702 --> 01:30:11.869
<i>and people at over 80 years old?</i>

01:30:11.871 --> 01:30:14.804
<i>I mean, what does that say about the
effect of concussions on players?</i>

01:30:14.806 --> 01:30:16.173
<i>I'm not a doctor here,</i>

01:30:16.175 --> 01:30:19.910
<i>but you have to look at
their entire medical history.</i>

01:30:19.912 --> 01:30:23.080
<i>This is an evolving
science. And that's okay.</i>

01:30:23.082 --> 01:30:25.883
<i>While I agree with the Commissioner,</i>

01:30:25.885 --> 01:30:30.653
<i>no empirically determined
proof was presented today.</i>

01:30:30.655 --> 01:30:33.490
<i>Because there simply isn't any.</i>

01:30:33.492 --> 01:30:36.494
<i>Because according to
the NFL's own numbers,</i>

01:30:36.496 --> 01:30:38.562
<i>half of all players with concussions</i>

01:30:38.564 --> 01:30:41.165
<i>are sent back into the same game,</i>

01:30:41.167 --> 01:30:44.504
<i>including some who were
actually knocked out cold.</i>

01:30:45.704 --> 01:30:48.104
<i>Ira Casson was head of the team of</i>

01:30:48.106 --> 01:30:50.708
<i>NFL doctors who had
looked into the issue</i>

01:30:50.710 --> 01:30:52.843
<i>and determined that the concern</i>

01:30:52.845 --> 01:30:55.211
<i>over head injuries was overblown.</i>

01:30:55.213 --> 01:30:58.516
<i>Is there any evidence, as
far as you're concerned,</i>

01:30:58.518 --> 01:31:00.584
<i>that links multiple head injuries</i>

01:31:00.586 --> 01:31:03.187
<i>among pro football
players with depression?</i>

01:31:03.189 --> 01:31:04.588
<i>No.</i>

01:31:04.590 --> 01:31:05.990
<i>With dementia?</i>

01:31:05.992 --> 01:31:07.590
<i>No.</i>

01:31:07.592 --> 01:31:09.527
<i>With early onset of Alzheimer's?</i>

01:31:09.529 --> 01:31:10.995
<i>No.</i>

01:31:10.997 --> 01:31:14.665
<i>Is there any evidence
as of today that links</i>

01:31:14.667 --> 01:31:18.869
<i>multiple head injuries with any
